Package: kxine
Version: 0.5
Revision: 0.20020924.1
Depends: libxine (>= 0.9.13-1), libxine-shlibs (>= 0.9.13-1), kdelibs3-ssl (>= 3.0.7-3) | kdelibs3 (>= 3.0.7-3), x11, dlcompat, libart2-shlibs, qt3-shlibs (>= 3.0.5-7), libpng-shlibs
BuildDepends: libpoll, libxine (>= 0.9.13-1), arts-dev (>= 1.0.7-3), kdelibs3-ssl-dev (>= 3.0.7-3) | kdelibs3-dev (>= 3.0.7-3), x11, dlcompat, libart2, qt3 (>= 3.0.5-7), libpng, libjpeg, automake (>= 1.6), libtool14, autoconf25
Maintainer: Benjamin Reed <ranger@befunk.com>
Source: http://ranger.befunk.com/fink/kxine-20020924.tar.bz2
SourceDirectory: kxine
PatchScript: sed 's|@PREFIX@|%p|g' <%a/%f.patch | patch -p0
SetLDFLAGS: -L%p/lib
SetCPPFLAGS: -no-cpp-precomp
SetCFLAGS: -I%p/include
ConfigureParams: --with-qt-dir=%p --with-xine-prefix=%p --with-extra-includes=%p/include --with-extra-libs=%p/lib
CompileScript: <<
#!/bin/sh
 export KDEDIR=%p
 export QTDIR=%p
 make -f Makefile.dist
 ./configure %c
 make -j4
<<
InstallScript: <<
 make install DESTDIR=%d
<<
Description: KDE DVD and video player.
DescDetail: <<
This program integrates the xine video and audio player into KDE. It
plays all formats xine supports.
<<
